{"type":"message","id":"0c13f110","parentId":"987c2608","timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:46:19.831Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the product-selector's models.json has OpenRouter with google/gemini-2.0-flash listed as an OpenRouter model. But the config says `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash`. The model id in OpenRouter is `google/gemini-2.0-flash`, not `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash`.\n\nOptions:\n1. Change the model in config from `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash` to `google/gemini-2.0-flash` (using OpenRouter)\n2. Add a `gemini` provider directly to product-selector's models.json with the Google AI API key\n\n\n3. The config references `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash` but OpenRouter's model ID is `google/gemini-2.0-flash` — I need to figure out which provider the config is actually trying to use and whether it matches what's available.\n\nThe simplest fix would be to either correct the model ID in the config to use the OpenRouter format, or add a direct `gemini` provider to the product-selector models.json and switch the config to use that instead. The second approach seems cleaner since the user specifically asked about the Gemini key and mentioned wanting to configure it for the selector. the config from `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash` to `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` so it references the direct Google AI provider, then add the `gemini` provider with that API key to the product-selector's models.json file. the config from `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash` to `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` to use the direct Google AI provider, and add the `gemini` provider configuration with the API key to the product-selector's models.json file."},{"type":"text","text":"Key 可用 ✓。问题在于 product-selector 的 config 和 models.json 不匹配：\n- config 写的是 `google-ai/gemini-2.0-flash`\n- 但 models.json 里只有 OpenRouter 的 `google/gemini-2.0-flash`\n\n我来把它改成直连 Google AI 的配置，用你的 key：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b1ek8mv1yr7r_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.ope