{"type":"message","id":"093708e6","parentId":"38137705","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:38:19.351Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the auth profile for product-selector uses gemini directly. But I should also make sure that new sessions would use gemini by default, not openrouter. The `authProfileOverrideSource: \"auto\"` means it was auto-selected. Let me check if there's a way to set a default auth profile for the agent.\n\nActually, the better fix would be to also set a default for the product-selector agent in its config or models.json. Let me also look at the models.json for the authProfile setting.\n\nActually, I think the core issue is that the `product-selector` agent's config.json specifies `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` but the system is falling back to `openrouter:default` because... it seems the models.json for the product-selector doesn't have the gemini provider properly wired, OR the agent config isn't being read from the right place.\n \nThe session's modelProvider is openrouter and it's using openrouter/free, which confirms the system is ignoring the agent's config.json model setting. The sessions.json has an `agent:product-selector:feishu:direct:...` session key that was created for a specific feishu direct message interaction. But now when HALEI talks to the \"选品agent\" through the main agent, it should spawn a new session or use a different routing mechanism—I'm not sure if this routing is even working correctly.\n\nThe `sessions_spawn` call should use the product-selector config, but it seems to be using the main agent's config instead, which suggests the spawning mechanism isn't properly reading the subagent's configuration."},{"type":"text","text":"还需要确保 product-selector 的 agent 配置里能引用到 gemini provider。让我看看它的完整目录结构：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ht6k6fw53ht7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector -type f -name \"*.json\" | xargs ls -la 2>/