{"type":"message","id":"a40ce826","parentId":"28bdc5a4","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:43:46.328Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the session still shows the old session f3bca540. But the user says they restarted and a new task was sent. The sessions.json might have been updated with a new session entry. Let me check the current status of the gateway and also check if there's a newer session.\n\nAlso, the user mentions the backend UI shows version 1.5 and didn't switch successfully. This suggests that maybe the UI's model selection is not properly connected to the agent's actual config.\n\nLet me think about what might be happening:\n1. The sessions.json shows `authProfileOverride: \"gemini:default\"` and `authProfileOverrideSource: \"manual\"` - this was updated\n\n\n2. But if the new session doesn't have this, the auto-override might kick in again and revert it back to `openrouter:default`\n\nI need to check if there are newer sessions in the file beyond the old f3bca540 session, and also look at the main agent's models.json to see if the UI's model selection is actually being reflected in the configuration."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1h5511ubpyl3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/sessions.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(k[:80], '->', v.get('model','?'), '| auth:', v.get('authProfileOverride','?')) for k,v in d.items()]\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775735015409,"responseId":"0626c3e70e27bc832f133e31e8fe27c9"}}
