{"type":"message","id":"b715ca89","parentId":"f605c522","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:44:01.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session still shows `openrouter/free` as the model. Even though authProfileOverride is set to `gemini:default`, the model itself is `openrouter/free`. The auth profile override controls the credentials, but the model selection seems to be happening at a different level.\n\nThe user mentions the UI shows version 1.5 and the switch didn't work. Let me think about how OpenClaw selects models for subagents.\n\nWhen a subagent is spawned via `sessions_spawn`, the model selection logic likely:\n1. Looks at the agent's config.json for the `model` field\n2. Or looks at the parent session's model\n3. Or uses some default\n   \nI should check if there's a system-wide default model setting that might be overriding the subagent configuration, since the product-selector config.json has `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` set but it's still using `openrouter/free`. The UI showing 1.5 is puzzling given the system prompt explicitly references 2.0, so maybe the actual model being used isn't respecting the config at all.\n\nLooking at the session data, the model is `openrouter/free` which suggests the system might be falling back to a default when the configured model isn't available or properly formatted in models.json. The UI label showing 1.5 could be a display bug or it might reflect what the system thinks is configured versus what's actually running.\n\nThe real issue seems to be that despite setting `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` in the agent config and `gemini:default` in the auth profile override, the subagent is still using `openrouter/free` instead. This points to either a model resolution problem where the system can't properly map the model name to an available provider, or the config changes weren't applied to the active session.\n\nI should check if there are other agent configuration files that might be taking precedence, or if the models.json for the main agent is overriding the product-selector settings. The fact that the UI displays gemini-1.5-flash while the config specifies 2.0 suggests there's a disconnect between what's configured and what the system is actually using."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x9ci90c8kldw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/halei/.openclaw -name \"openclaw.json\" | head -3"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x9ci90c8kldw_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/halei/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" | xargs grep -l \"defaultModel\\|default_model\\|fallback\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775735026508,"responseId":"0626c3f23488f198c43b50ec211fffcb"}}
