{"type":"message","id":"70f455f8","parentId":"ca31548f","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:44:31.326Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue! Looking at the openclaw.json:\n\n```json\n\"subagents\": {\n  \"allowAgents\": [\n    \"*\"\n  ],\n  \"model\": {\n    \"primary\": \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe subagent model is set to `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash`, NOT `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`. And the `agents.defaults.model.primary` is `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7`.\n\nBut wait, the product-selector agent has its own config with `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`.\n\n\nSo the product-selector's config should override the subagent defaults, but something's still wrong. The UI is showing `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash` instead of `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`, which means the product-selector config isn't being picked up properly. Let me trace through the config chain again to see where the override is getting lost.\n\nActually, I need to understand how the agent catalog works—when I use `agent:product-selector`, it's loading from the agents directory, but the UI is somehow showing `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash` instead of `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`. Maybe there's a mismatch between what the config says and what the UI is actually reading, or the product-selector agent config isn't being applied the way I expect.\n\nWait, the user mentioned \"后台ui页面\" - they're looking at the gateway's web UI, not the agent logs. The UI might be reading from a different config source or displaying a cached value. Let me check if the gateway's control UI is pulling from openclaw.json defaults instead of the agent-specific config. And there's something odd about the `auth: { profiles: {...} }` section showing `openrouter:default` but not `gemini:default` in the global auth - though that shouldn't matter since the product-selector has its own auth-profiles.json.\n\nThe real problem might be that `product-selector` isn't registered as an agent in openclaw.json's agents list at all. The main session only shows `main` and `tts` agents, so when spawning `agent:product-selector`, it might be falling back to the subagent default model of `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash` instead of using the config from `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/agent/config.json`.\n\nI should add `product-selector` to the agents list in openclaw.json with the proper agentDir pointing to its config directory."},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了。看 `openclaw.json` 的 `agents.list` 配置：\n\n```json\n\"agents\": {\n  \"defaults\": {\n    \"model\": {\n      \"primary\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"fallbacks\": [\"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n而 `agents.list` 里只有 `main` 和 `tts`，**没有 `product-selector`**。这意味着选品 Agent 根本不在正式注册名单里，可能被当作了临时 subagent 处理，用的是 subagent 默认配置 `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash`。\n\n需要把 product-selector 正式注册进去。我来改：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2r6ex06xqodr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\n\n# Find the agents section\nagents = d.get('agents', {})\nagent_list = agents.get('list', [])\n\n# Check if product-selector already exists\nps_exists = any(a.get('id') == 'product-selector' for a in agent_list)\nprint('product-selector in list:', ps_exists)\nprint('Current agents:', [a.get('id') for a in agent_list])\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775735046797,"responseId":"0626c4076b3566f5f3cef481ff42cb1b"}}
