{"type":"message","id":"c9eb1638","parentId":"8018db31","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:52:05.277Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[media attached: /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/bf470a88-2c25-40a2-bfc3-6786e9c95dfc.jpg (image/jpeg) | /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/bf470a88-2c25-40a2-bfc3-6786e9c95dfc.jpg]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Avoid absolute paths (MEDIA:/...) and ~ paths - they are blocked for security. Keep caption in the text body.\nSystem: [2026-04-09 19:51:45 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b524d63ce14a8c4a05e9be37a7cf, post, 1 attachment(s)]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b524d63ce14a8c4a05e9be37a7cf\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-09 19:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/bf470a88-2c25-40a2-bfc3-6786e9c95dfc.jpg\n怎么把TTS 还钱给去掉了。两个分不清楚那个了"}],"timestamp":1775735525246}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd16bfc2","parentId":"c9eb1638","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:52:22.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent an image showing that TTS (the Feishu account name) now shows no money/credit indicator, and they're saying \"怎么把TTS 还钱给去掉了。两个分不清楚那个了\" - meaning the TTS account's \"money\" or credit indicator has been removed, and now they can't tell which account is which.\n\nLooking at the image, it seems the TTS account in Feishu no longer shows a money/balance indicator, making it hard to distinguish from the main kiit account.\n\nWait, I think the user is saying that the TTS account name used to have some money indicator or visual marker, but now it's gone, making it hard to tell TTS and kiit apart.\n \nI should clarify what actually changed. When I modified the selector agent to use tts as its ID, I may have inadvertently affected how the TTS account appears in Feishu's interface. The missing money/credit indicator was likely a side effect of that configuration change, not something I intentionally removed. I need to check if restoring the original TTS configuration would bring back that distinguishing marker. Looking at the bindings configuration, the agentId was successfully switched to 'selector', so the issue might be elsewhere in how the account displays. The user is pointing out that the TTS account is missing its money/credit indicator in the sidebar, which is making it harder to distinguish between the two accounts—this could be affecting how the kiit account appears as well.\n\nI should check if this is related to how OpenClaw handles channel account registration or if there's a display issue with the bindings configuration itself."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fak3xnkzjb08_1","name":"image","arguments":{"prompt":"Describe what you see in this image, focusing on any Feishu account names, indicators, or labels visible in a list or sidebar.","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/bf470a88-2c25-40a2-bfc3-6786e9c95dfc.jpg"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775735525297,"responseId":"0626c5e55cb1b566db48af6d5f162390"}}
{"type":"message","id":"db927309","parentId":"fd16bfc2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:52:46.936Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fak3xnkzjb08_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the provided image, here are the account names, indicators, and labels found within the sidebars and lists. While you mentioned Feishu, the interface appears to be a specialized AI agent management platform (potentially related to a project called \"Openclaw,\" as seen in the file path).\n\n### 1. Left Sidebar Navigation Labels\nThe sidebar on the left contains the primary navigation labels for the application:\n*   **聊天 (Chat):** The top menu item.\n*   **控制 (Control):** A navigation category.\n*   **代理 (Agent):** The currently selected navigation item, highlighted with a red background and a folder icon.\n*   **技能 (Skills):** A navigation item with a lightning bolt icon.\n*   **节点 (Nodes):** A navigation item with a square icon.\n\n### 2. Dropdown List (Personas/Account Indicators)\nA dropdown menu is open in the center of the screen, which lists specific \"identities\" or \"agents\" that act as account-style indicators:\n*   **main (default):** This is the currently selected option, highlighted in grey.\n*   **选品专家 (Xuǎnpǐn zhuānjiā):** Translates to \"Selection Expert\" or \"Product Selection Specialist.\" This label appears twice in the list.\n\n### 3. User and Content Labels\nOther indicators and labels visible in the main content area include:\n*   **代理 (Agent):** The main header of the page.\n*   **工作区、工具、身份 (Workspace, Tools, Identity):** A descriptive label/subhead under the main header.\n*   **halei:** This name appears within the workspace file path indicator: `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace`. This acts as the system user name.\n*   **Bottom Tab Labels:** A horizontal list of labels at the bottom of the section: `AGENTS`, `SOUL`, `TOOLS`, `IDENTITY`, `USER`, and `HEARTBEAT`.\n*   **Top Right Labels:** Smaller labels for `Channels` and `Cron Jobs`."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/bf470a88-2c25-40a2-bfc3-6786e9c95dfc.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775735566922}}
{"type":"message","id":"4c3452f2","parentId":"db927309","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:52:59.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The image shows the OpenClaw control panel. The dropdown shows two \"选品专家\" entries - one is probably the old TTS and one is the product-selector. The issue is that after my edits, the \"TTS\" agent's name still shows \"TTS-选品专家\" in the config but the user is seeing something different in the UI.\n\nActually, looking at the UI - there are two \"选品专家\" entries. One is the \"tts\" agent (product selector) and one is the \"product-selector\" agent I added. The user is confused because both show the same name.\n\nThe user says \"TTS 还钱给去掉了\" - meaning the TTS account name/labels got removed and now they can't distinguish between the two accounts. \n\n\nI realize I should have kept the original \"TTS-选品专家\" naming to preserve that visual distinction in the interface. Now I'm checking the current configuration to see what names are actually being displayed."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n9uldf1tmiwz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\nfor agent in d['agents']['list']:\n    print(f\\\"id={agent['id']}, name={agent.get('name','?')}, model={agent.get('model','?')}, agentDir={agent.get('agentDir','?')}\\\")\nprint()\nprint('bindings:', json.dumps(d.get('bindings', []), ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\nprint()\nchannels = d.get('channels', {}).get('feishu', {}).get('accounts', {})\nfor k, v in channels.items():\n    print(f\\\"feishu account: {k}, name={v.get('name','?')}\\\")\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775735566938,"responseId":"0626c60f02bda5744e493ceaeffb9e60"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dcc7febe","parentId":"4c3452f2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:52:59.888Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n9uldf1tmiwz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"id=main, name=?, model=minimax/MiniMax-M2.7, agentDir=/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main\nid=tts, name=选品专家, model=gemini/gemini-2.0-flash, agentDir=/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\nid=product-selector, name=选品专家, model=gemini/gemini-2.0-flash, agentDir=/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/agent\n\nbindings: [\n  {\n    \"agentId\": \"tts\",\n    \"match\": {\n      \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"accountId\": \"tts\"\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"agentId\": \"main\",\n    \"match\": {\n      \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"accountId\": \"kiit\"\n    }\n  }\n]\n\nfeishu account: kiit, name=kiit\nfeishu account: tts, name=TK 选品大师"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":79,"aggregated":"id=main, name=?, model=minimax/MiniMax-M2.7, agentDir=/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main\nid=tts, name=选品专家, model=gemini/gemini-2.0-flash, agentDir=/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\nid=product-selector, name=选品专家, model=gemini/gemini-2.0-flash, agentDir=/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/agent\n\nbindings: [\n  {\n    \"agentId\": \"tts\",\n    \"match\": {\n      \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"accountId\": \"tts\"\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"agentId\": \"main\",\n    \"match\": {\n      \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"accountId\": \"kiit\"\n    }\n  }\n]\n\nfeishu account: kiit, name=kiit\nfeishu account: tts, name=TK 选品大师","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775735579873}}
{"type":"message","id":"369bad5a","parentId":"dcc7febe","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:53:12.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. There are 3 agents: `main`, `tts`, `product-selector`\n2. Both `tts` and `product-selector` have name \"选品专家\" - that's the duplication in the dropdown\n3. The feishu account `tts` is named \"TK 选品大师\" (TK product master)\n4. Binding: `tts` agent handles feishu account `tts`, `main` handles feishu account `kiit`\n\nThe user is confused because there are two agents both called \"选品专家\" in the dropdown. \n\nSo the real problem is that `product-selector` shouldn't exist as a separate agent at all - it's redundant when `tts` already handles the product selection work. I need to remove `product-selector` from the agents list to clean this up. The feishu account `tts` (TK 选品大师) is what actually routes to the TTS agent, so removing the duplicate selector agent makes sense—though I'd lose the `kiit` binding if I delete it entirely. But actually, that binding's unnecessary since `kiit` is already handled by the main agent, so I can safely remove `product-selector` without breaking anything."},{"type":"text","text":"明白了——\"选品专家\"出现了两次，因为 `tts` 和 `product-selector` 都叫这个名字，而且 feishu 里的 tts 账户名字是\"TK 选品大师\"，其实就是一个东西。\n\n我来把 `product-selector` 删掉，避免重复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gbjm5p1s923n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\nbefore = [a['id'] for a in d['agents']['list']]\nd['agents']['list'] = [a for a in d['agents']['list'] if a['id'] != 'product-selector']\nafter = [a['id'] for a in d['agents']['list']]\n\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(d, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\nprint('Before:', before)\nprint('After:', after)\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775735579890,"responseId":"0626c61c55f381617c87c2097a9e02d5"}}
