{"type":"message","id":"6afc3988","parentId":"9acd50d1","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:01:47.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw.json is correct - the tts agent has `\"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\"`. But the UI shows \"Inherit default (minimax/MiniMax-M2.7)\". \n\nThis means the UI might not be reading from openclaw.json but from a different source (perhaps the agent's own config.json or the database). Or it could be a UI display lag.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the UI is showing what it has in its local state vs. what's actually saved in openclaw.json. The gateway reads openclaw.json at startup, but the UI might be displaying cached/projected values.\n\nThe UI says \"Inherit default\" but the overview section at top shows `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` as the Primary Model summary. \n\nWait, I'm re-reading the description: \"Primary Model (Summary Display): gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\" and \"Primary model: Inherit default (minimax/MiniMax-M2.7)\". These seem contradictory. Maybe \"Inherit default\" is just the UI element showing the raw config value, while the actual model being used (shown in summary) is gemini-2.0-flash. Or perhaps the UI is distinguishing between what's configured versus what's actually active.\n\nI should just reload the gateway config through the UI to see if it picks up the openclaw.json changes. But I'm also wondering if the UI is pulling agent configs from a completely different source than openclaw.json, like the agentDir itself. Let me check what's actually in the tts agent config file, since it returned empty earlier."},{"type":"text","text":"openclaw.json 里的配置是对的，`model: gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`。但 UI 显示 \"Inherit default\" 可能是读取源不同步。\n\n让我检查一下 tts agent 目录里还有什么配置文件：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5uyh0537kktu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts -type f | sort"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model