{"type":"message","id":"d274bb52","parentId":"96f673b5","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:02:18.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tts/agent directory has NO `config.json`! There's only `auth-profiles.json` and `models.json`. The agentDir points to `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent` but there's no config.json there.\n\nThis means when the system looks for the agent config, it won't find a `config.json` in the agentDir. The `model` field from `openclaw.json` should override, but maybe the UI is reading from a different source.\n\nWait - the `agents.list[].model` in openclaw.json IS the model config. But the UI might be reading from a different config file or a cached state.\n \nLooking at the openclaw.json structure, the tts agent entry doesn't have a nested `config.json` override - it's all defined inline. So the UI's \"Inherit default\" message likely means the agent's model config is being read as \"use agent default\" rather than something explicit, which is why it's falling back to the system default of minimax/MiniMax-M2.7. The UI is probably reading from a completely different configuration source than openclaw.json - it's pulling from the agent's own config.json file in /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent/, which doesn't exist, so it's defaulting to the system minimax model instead. The tts agent might not have its own config.json file in the expected location, or the UI could be pulling from a different data source altogether—maybe it's reading from openclaw.json but interpreting the model field differently than I expect. Let me try reloading the gateway config to see if that resolves the inconsistency between what the UI displays and what the actual configuration shows."},{"type":"text","text":"问题找到了——tts 的 agentDir（`/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent`）里**没有 config.json**，只有 models.json 和 auth-profiles.json。没有 config.json 就没有模型声明，UI 只能显示继承默认值。\n\n补上 config.json：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_