{"type":"message","id":"3f218cbf","parentId":"4d180426","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:09:02.611Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session shows `authProfileOverride: minimax:cn` and `model: MiniMax-M2.7`. The model is MiniMax, not gemini-2.0-flash.\n\nThe issue is that even though the agent config says `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`, the session is using `MiniMax-M2.7` via the `minimax:cn` auth profile override.\n\nThe `authProfileOverride` is set to `minimax:cn`, which means it's using the minimax provider. This overrides the agent's configured model.\n\nI need to understand the auth profile resolution. The `minimax:cn` auth profile is defined in the main openclaw.json:\n\n\n```json\n\"auth\": {\n  \"profiles\": {\n    \"minimax:cn\": {\n      \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n      \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo the session has an auth profile override of `minimax:cn`, which forces the minimax provider. But the tts agent config says `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`. The auth profile override seems to be forcing the model/provider independently of the agent config.\n\nThis session is running (`status: running`), so it's an active session. The auth profile override of `minimax:cn` is likely coming from the feishu channel binding. When the tts feishu account was first set up, it probably got assigned the minimax:cn auth profile automatically.\n\nLooking at the channel config for the feishu tts account, it may be specifying the auth profile. The real issue is that the session is using minimax:cn override, but if the tts agent's models.json has the gemini provider configured, it should use gemini. The auth profile override is forcing minimax, which contradicts what the agent config expects. If the user is saying the AI isn't responding with gemini-2.0-flash even though it's configured in the UI, the problem is likely that the running session has an auth profile override of `minimax:cn` that was set before the config change. The UI shows the config correctly now, but the active session is still using the old minimax model. Since the session status is \"running,\" the user might be in an active conversation where the agent is still using the old model. I should suggest either starting a new session or updating the auth profile override to `gemini:default` to force gemini-2.0-flash."},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！当前 tts 的活跃 session 绑定的是 `authProfileOverride: minimax:cn`，强制使用 MiniMax 模型。这是飞书 tts 账户创建时默认绑定的认证配置。\n\n需要把它改成 gemini：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qlmvc3ppwbxx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/sessions.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor k, v in d.items():\n    print('Session:', k)\n    print('  authProfileOverride:', v.get('authProfileOverride'))\n    print('  authProfileOverrideSource:', v.get('authProfileOverrideSource'))\n    print('  status:', v.get('status'))\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775736521573,"responseId":"0626c9c948643c048f1083e8c9546d2b"}}
