{"type":"message","id":"6e43d7cc","parentId":"8ba5ed4c","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:23:32.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the session now has:\n- `modelOverride: \"MiniMax-M2.7\"`\n- `providerOverride: \"minimax\"`\n\nThese override fields are taking precedence over the config. The session-level overrides are probably set by the channel binding or some auto-detection logic. These session overrides were set automatically, likely from the channel config.\n\nThe key issue is `providerOverride: \"minimax\"` and `modelOverride: \"MiniMax-M2.7\"` - these are session-level overrides that bypass the agent config.\n\nI need to remove these overrides from the session. But actually, these might be set by the channel when the agent is spawned. The channel config for tts might be specifying minimax.\n \nLooking at the session more carefully, it was created at 20:19 (Unix 1775737308653 = April 9, 2026 12:41:48 UTC = 20:41 CST, so this is a new session). The binding for tts uses the tts accountId, but I need to check if the channel configuration itself is enforcing minimax as the provider.\n\nThe channel config for feishu has accountId \"tts\" with an appId and appSecret, but the account-level config doesn't explicitly set a model override. Since this is a new session created after my fixes, the `modelOverride: \"MiniMax-M2.7\"` might be coming from the agent's default behavior. The openclaw.json tts agent config has `\"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\"`, but the session is still using MiniMax instead.\n\nThe real issue is that `modelOverride` at the session level is taking precedence over the agent config. I should check if there's a binding-level override or if the session itself is enforcing the MiniMax model, since deleting the session would force a new one to pick up the agent's intended config."},{"type":"text","text":"看到了，session 里有 `modelOverride: \"MiniMax-M2.7\"` 和 `providerOverride: \"minimax\"`，这个 session 级别的覆盖优先级比 agent 配置更高。\n\n这是 channel 初始化 session 时自动写入的。需要删掉这个 session 让它重新建：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_trw0x0c3otl7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/sessions.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nsession_key = 'agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68'\nif session_key in d:\n    print('Found session, removing modelOverride and providerOverride')\n    d[session_key].pop('modelOverride', None)\n    d[session_key].pop('providerOverride', None)\n    d[session_key]['authProfileOverride'] = 'gemini:default'\n    d[session_key]['authProfileOverrideSource'] = 'manual'\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/sessions.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(d, f, indent=2)\nprint('Done')\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775737392405,"responseId":"0626cd318c91ec14b807bcffd55c97d9"}}
