elf. So if footer.zh_cn was set to empty, the thinking card footer would be empty, but the card content \"思考中...\" itself wouldn't be affected.\n\nLet me just try setting footer.zh_cn to empty and see if that helps.\n\nActually, I think the real issue might be that I need to understand the full picture. Let me check if the footer config affects the thinking card at all.\n\nLet me just try: set footer.show/zhong to false or empty.\n\nActually, I think I'm overcomplicating this. The user said \"I'm saying to close this prompt, not to close the thinking mode.\" So they want to close the \"思考中\" indicator but keep thinking enabled.\n\nThe footer config might be the right place. Let me look at the footer schema more carefully.\n\nLooking at the schema, footer is optional and has properties like `elapsed` and `status` for timestamps. It doesn't seem to have a `content` field that would control the \"思考中...\" text itself.\n\nLet me try setting footer to something minimal like `{\"content\": { \"zh_cn\": \"\" }}` to see if that suppresses the thinking indicator.\n\nActually, I should just try several approaches: disable footer entirely, set content to empty strings, and check if there are any other config options I'm missing in the schema.\n\nThe user wants to keep thinking mode on but just hide the \"思考中...\" text that appears during processing. Maybe they're asking for the thinking content to be suppressed in the UI while still allowing the actual reasoning to happen.\n\nI'm overcomplicating this. Let me just try a few practical fixes: setting footer.content to empty, disabling footer completely, or using the `replyMode: \"static\"` setting instead of streaming, which might suppress the thinking indicator while keeping reasoning enabled."},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。\"思考中\"是 streaming 模式的 thinking card，不是 footer 里的文字。试试把 replyMode 改成 static，这会完全停用 streaming card 的 thinking 提示，但不影响 AI 思考本身：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_olxkbcmhekhs_1","name":"exec","arguments