d prevent the thinking card from displaying at all. But if the thinking card is still showing, maybe the default isn't what I expect, or there's a mismatch between what I think the code is doing and what's actually happening. Let me take a concrete approach and just look at what's actually configured rather than continuing to reason through the code. I'm wondering if there's a channel-level streaming option that's somehow overriding the per-account setting, or maybe the issue is elsewhere entirely. The piano emoji is likely just Feishu's native typing indicator, which the plugin wouldn't control through its config anyway. Let me step back and actually check what the code does versus what the user is experiencing—I'll ask them to confirm whether the thinking card has actually disappeared after our changes, or if they're still seeing it in the current session. The thinking card should only appear during streaming, so with streaming disabled the thinking card shouldn't show. But I should check if the feishu plugin itself is doing something different before the thinking card renders, or if there's a race condition where an old message is still being processed. Maybe the user is seeing the wrong thing. Let me ask them to send a fresh message right now and tell me if the thinking indicator still appears - that would tell me if my fix is actually working."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6mmem0znd78q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"replyMode\\|useStreamingCards\\|ensureCardCreated\\|controller\" /home/halei/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/src/card/reply-dispatcher.js | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775739187828,"responseId":"0626d4347af6fdf4a636d21dac8d5948"}}
