ing: None\n  modelOverride: None\n\nSession: agent:main:cron:7d79be6c-d181-45c1-b57f-209a245c060e:run:941cc1e1-065c-4aee-ba5e\n  streaming: None\n  modelOverride: None","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739259458}}
{"type":"message","id":"3385833f","parentId":"d5b9cf35","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:54:36.474Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The main session shows `streaming: None` and `modelOverride: None`. The session doesn't seem to be overriding anything.\n\nBut the \"思考中\" is still showing up. Let me look at this from a different angle - maybe the streaming is being used at the Feishu message level, not the channel config level. Maybe there's a per-session streaming setting.\n\nActually wait - let me look at the session more carefully. The `agent:main:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` session is the main KIIT session, not the TTS session. And it shows `streaming: None`.\n \nSo I'm realizing that KIIT is the main assistant running on the kiit Feishu account, while TTS is the product selector agent on a separate Feishu account. When the user sends a message to KIIT, they're interacting with the main session, and the streaming settings should be per-account based on the kiit account configuration.\n\nThe user is complaining that KIIT is showing the thinking indicator when they send messages, which suggests KIIT has streaming enabled on the kiit account. I set kiit's streaming to False and restarted the gateway, but the user is still seeing it. I'm wondering if there's a timing issue where the gateway restarted mid-conversation and the session got recreated with the old streaming behavior, or if there's something about how feishu long-polling reconnects that I'm missing.\n\nActually, I think I finally understand what's happening. The messages showing \"思考中\" aren't from the KIIT bot at all—they're from the OpenClaw gateway itself. When you send a message to the gateway through Feishu, it echoes back with those typing indicators and piano emojis as it processes and forwards the message to the AI. That's the streaming behavior at the gateway level, separate from the KIIT bot's streaming setting.\n\nBut the user is saying they disabled it and it's still showing up. I'm wondering if the kiit account streaming config is actually being applied correctly, or if the gateway is falling back to the channel-level config because the account-specific setting isn't being read. Let me check the gateway's log to see what configuration it's actually using."},{"type":"text","text":"让我查一下 gateway 日志，看它实际读到的 streaming 配置是什么：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_am3oaa0sp2lh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -u openclaw --no-pager -n 30 2>/dev/null | tail -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775739259483,"responseId":"0626d47b21a6e736afc1a79185347f24"}}
