{"type":"message","id":"c02e896a","parentId":"20356f1a","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:57:03.360Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b8w4gld81l24_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const handler_registry_1 = require(\"./handler-registry.js\");\nconst dispatch_1 = require(\"./dispatch.js\");\nconst policy_1 = require(\"./policy.js\");\nconst logger = (0, lark_logger_1.larkLogger)('inbound/handler');\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Public: handle inbound message\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nasync function handleFeishuMessage(params) {\n    const { cfg, event, botOpenId, runtime, chatHistories, accountId, replyToMessageId, forceMention, skipTyping } = params;\n    // 1. Account resolution\n    const account = (0, accounts_1.getLarkAccount)(cfg, accountId);\n    const accountFeishuCfg = account.config;\n    // ★ 多账号配置隔离：构造 account 级别的 ClawdbotConfig\n    //\n    //   在多账号场景下，每个 account 可以独立配置 groupPolicy / requireMention\n    //   等策略。但 SDK 的 resolveGroupPolicy / resolveRequireMention 等函数从\n    //   cfg.channels.feishu 读取配置，而 cfg 是顶层全局配置，不包含 per-account\n    //   的覆盖值。\n    //\n    //   这里将 cfg.channels.feishu 替换为经过 getLarkAccount() 合并后的\n    //   accountFeishuCfg（= base config + account override），确保下游所有 SDK 调用\n    //   都能正确读取当前 account 的配置。\n    const accountScopedCfg = {\n        ...cfg,\n        channels: { ...cfg.channels, feishu: accountFeishuCfg },\n    };\n    const log = runtime?.log ?? ((...args) => logger.info(args.map(String).join(' ')));\n    const error = runtime?.error ?? ((...args) => logger.error(args.map(String).join(' ')));\n    // 2. Parse event → MessageContext (merge_forward expanded in-place)\n    let ctx = await (0, parse_1.parseMessageEvent)(event, botOpenId, {\n        cfg: accountScopedCfg,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":60,"aggregated":"const handler_registry_1 = require(\"./handler-registry.js\");\nconst dispatch_1 = require(\"./dispatch.js\");\nconst policy_1 = require(\"./policy.js\");\nconst logger = (0, lark_logger_1.larkLogger)('inbound/handler');\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Public: handle inbound message\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nasync function handleFeishuMessage(params) {\n    const { cfg, event, botOpenId, runtime, chatHistories, accountId, replyToMessageId, forceMention, skipTyping } = params;\n    // 1. Account resolution\n    const account = (0, accounts_1.getLarkAccount)(cfg, accountId);\n    const accountFeishuCfg = account.config;\n    // ★ 多账号配置隔离：构造 account 级别的 ClawdbotConfig\n    //\n    //   在多账号场景下，每个 account 可以独立配置 groupPolicy / requireMention\n    //   等策略。但 SDK 的 resolveGroupPolicy / resolveRequireMention 等函数从\n    //   cfg.channels.feishu 读取配置，而 cfg 是顶层全局配置，不包含 per-account\n    //   的覆盖值。\n    //\n    //   这里将 cfg.channels.feishu 替换为经过 getLarkAccount() 合并后的\n    //   accountFeishuCfg（= base config + account override），确保下游所有 SDK 调用\n    //   都能正确读取当前 account 的配置。\n    const accountScopedCfg = {\n        ...cfg,\n        channels: { ...cfg.channels, feishu: accountFeishuCfg },\n    };\n    const log = runtime?.log ?? ((...args) => logger.info(args.map(String).join(' ')));\n    const error = runtime?.error ?? ((...args) => logger.error(args.map(String).join(' ')));\n    // 2. Parse event → MessageContext (merge_forward expanded in-place)\n    let ctx = await (0, parse_1.parseMessageEvent)(event, botOpenId, {\n        cfg: accountScopedCfg,","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739423342}}
{"type":"message","id":"5806d89f","parentId":"c02e896a","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:57:27.497Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `skipTyping` is passed from the inbound handler to the reply dispatcher. But I need to find where the typing indicator start callback is actually called, and what controls whether it fires.Looking at the reply dispatcher code:\n```js\nconst typingCallbacks = (0, channel_runtime_1.createTypingCallbacks)({\n    keepaliveIntervalMs: 0,\n    start: async () => {\n        if (shouldSkip('typing.start.precheck'))\n            return;\n        if (!replyToMessageId || typingStopped || params.skipTyping)\n            return;\n        if (typingState?.reactionId)\n            return;\n        typingState = await (0, typing_1.addTypingIndicator)({...});\n```\n\nThe typing indicator start is triggered by `createTypingCallbacks`. This is called when the agent starts streaming/generating. In streaming mode, it's triggered when the first token arrives. In static mode, I'm not sure how it's triggered.\n\nBut the key question is: is there a config to disable the typing indicator entirely?\n\nLooking at the logging:\n```\n\"feishu[kiit][msg:...]: added typing indicator reaction\"\n```\n\nThis happens even in static mode (effectiveReplyMode=static, useStreamingCards=false). So the typing indicator is separate from streaming cards.\n\nThe typing indicator is the \"钢琴\" emoji reaction that appears on user messages in Feishu. The user wants to disable this.\n\nLooking at the typing.js code - it's about adding an emoji reaction. The config that controls whether typing indicators are added at all seems to be `skipTyping` which is passed as a parameter.\n\nIs there a per-account or global config to disable typing indicators? I don't see one in the schema. \n\nThe typing indicator appears to be a fundamental feature that gets added automatically for all replies. But wait—the user said the thinking indicator disappeared after disabling streaming. That钢琴 emoji might actually be the thinking indicator in Feishu, not a separate typing feature. So when streaming is disabled, the thinking card doesn't appear, but the emoji reaction might still be getting added through a different mechanism.\n\nLooking at the logging, the typing indicator is being added via an emoji reaction on the user's message, which is separate from the streaming card. The user is seeing that emoji and wants it gone, but I don't see a per-account config to disable typing indicators—the only skip mechanism is `skipTyping` in the handler, which is passed as a parameter. The typing indicator is added in the reply dispatcher regardless of streaming mode, and there's no global config to turn it off per account.\n\nI'm wondering if there's a `blockStreaming` config that might control this, or if the thinking indicator the user mentioned is actually the streaming card itself. Let me check the blockStreaming config to see if it affects the typing indicator.\n\nLooking at the reply-dispatcher logic, `blockStreaming` only applies when `useStreamingCards` is false, so it won't help here. I think the best path forward is to ask the user to clarify exactly which indicator they're referring to—whether it's the钢琴 emoji reaction, the \"思考中\" text, or something else—so I can determine if there's a config or code change that would actually fix it.\n\nWait, the user might be referring to the thinking indicator card that appears in streaming mode, which displays \"思考中...\" as a placeholder. Even with streaming disabled and static mode enabled, that thinking card could still be showing up. The config schema confirms that `ReplyModeValue` includes 'static' mode, so static mode should work—but I need to verify the actual streaming configuration to see why the thinking indicator is still appearing."},{"type":"text","text":"日志显示配置是正确的：`effectiveReplyMode=static`，`useStreamingCards=false`。但 typing indicator 还是在加。这是通过飞书 emoji reaction 实现的，不是 streaming 卡的思考提示。\n\n你说的\"钢琴小头像\"和\"思考中\"是在一起的吗？还是两个不同的提示？能截图给我看一下具体是哪个吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775739423365,"responseId":"0626d51fdf8d1dc2460e4adfd1c1e097"}}
